.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET-PIN-CHECK" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet-pin-check \- verify a PIN against the stored hash
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet-pin-check
.I wallet
.I pin
.SH DESCRIPTION
Hashes
.I pin
with SHA-256 and compares it to the stored
.B pin_hash
in the wallet database.
Returns
.B {"ok":true,"match":true}
on success or
.B {"ok":true,"match":false}
on mismatch.
The PIN is never stored in plain text.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true,"match":true|false}
{"ok":false,"reason":...}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-wallet-pin-set (1),
.BR lightning-wallet-check (1)
